      "content": "The push for these lessons in schools is fundamentally rooted in the belief that education must reflect modern realities and protect vulnerable students. Advocates see it as essential for creating a safe, affirming space where every child feels seen and respected. Those who oppose it are often driven by a desire to maintain traditional structures and shield children from what they perceive as ideological indoctrination. Therefore, the consensus is that a truly healthy educational environment must prioritize the well-being and acceptance of every single student.",
      "source": "target",
